-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Model captures registration of a flight operation with pre/post states, permission-based authorization, and interface constraints.
-- Summary 2: Added concrete resource FlightDB_Resource and assigned permissions to actors to fix type errors and missing facts.
-- Summary 3: All invariants, safety assertions, and test scenarios are type-correct and structurally consistent.
-- Assumption 1: The flight database is modeled as a single resource (FlightDB_Resource) owned by Airline_Operations_Team and accessible by relevant actors.
-- Assumption 2: Pre-state Pre1 represents the logged-in flight dispatcher; no finer-grained state details are modeled.
-- Assumption 3: Post-state Post1 represents successful flight registration; error states are abstracted as state changes.
-- Assumption 4: Permissions for actors are assigned minimally: Flight_Dispatchers have Read+Write+Admin, others have broader sets.
-- Open issue 1: Edge case assertions (ec_safe_1) may be too strong by forbidding any two Write operations to share a resource; could be refined to model unique flight numbers per resource instance.
-- Open issue 2: Non-functional invariants (e.g., nfr_fact_simultaneous_ops) may over-constrain the system; some checks may be unsatisfiable with scope 5.
-- Open issue 3: The model does not represent actual flight data (numbers, times, codes); test cases rely on abstract state changes.


